        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-11-12 20:15:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nPrakash, is it possible for you guys at LLNL to try this patch, along with the reverted patch of LU-2622(commit: 93fe562c), to see if the lock contention of lu_env cache still exists? If it still exists, I will create a patch for percpu cache.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "bd1b5ec96144eb748cbf605c2f7016e2cec0e875",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-12 22:28:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI was just thinking the same thing, that it'd be good to test these out on our Sequoia test system. I _think_ this patch will be enough, but testing on a many-core system would be best. I'll see if I can get it tested in the near future.\n\nWhat do you mean by a \"per cpu\" cache?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "ef542877500e885abddfcdd9c3d524fda05ec7a2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-11-13 17:28:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nYes, I think this patch would be enough to fix the lock contention as well. I have prepared another patch(didn't submit to gerrit yet) which will maintain percpu cache, and if this patch can't fix the problem I will submit it.\n\nI'm sorry that you guys are upset because of reverting the patch at LU-2622, but believe me that I'm working out something better.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
